##From the red zone of Vulcan Mountain, | we don't get emotional, we get physical!

Sh-scalpel

Functional introduction, Shanghai Medical Surgical cattle gathering place, your side of the surgical experts.

Medical history
Today's medical history is tomorrow's medical history

[ intro ]

The monitors flashed red and squealed, the goggles fogged up, the four gloved fingers were less flexible than usual, and the threat of Aerosol travel hung in the air, think about how to avoid the complications of intubation

This extraordinary intubation is a physical and psychological test of both.

On January 24th, at 4:30 am, I was suddenly told that I was going to Wuhan that night to fight the COVID-19 epidemic.

As a soldier, when you give an order, you do your duty.

During the day, we held an oath-taking mobilization meeting and prepared temporary supplies. At night, when we had a family reunion dinner, we boarded the army's special plane and headed for the front line in Wuhan, reaching the core of the battlefield.

Looking at the military transport aircraft on the tarmac, I suddenly remembered the 2008 earthquake in Wenchuan County, the same plane that took me to Mianyang.

It was more a hint, rather than a coincidence, that we would be back in style, just as we were back in Wenchuan County.

And when the medical team assembled, I found that I was the old comrades in this medical team, I told myself no matter what must be calm, help these young comrades-in-arms colleagues, give them courage and strength. The Hospital Party Committee appointed me to be the deputy group leader of the Long March medical team. I felt more responsible and made a secret determination that we would complete the task successfully. At the same time, we must do our own protection well to achieve the goal of zero infection.

On the second day of the eighth lunar month, I joined the 79-member Naval Medical University team and took over the Wuhan Hankou Hospital, a Grade III, class A hospital hospital and a designated COVID-19 hospital in Wuhan, the whole hospital has been devoted to the treatment and prevention of severe pneumonia.

Twelve doctors from our Long March Hospital were assigned to the intensive-care unit, put on thick protective clothing and goggles, and entered the ICU ward. I was shocked by what I saw. The infection of the medical staff at Hankou Hospital made us realize that the risk was at hand, a patient took my hand and said, "thank you, thank the PLA! "

We are moved by what we say from the heart.

Turning grief into action, turning grief into courage, we adapted to the environment, optimized protective procedures, carefully designed treatment programs, after a week of treatment work, glad to see that patients can walk out of the hospital.

After that, we moved to Vulcan Mountain Hospital.

According to the arrangement of the medical team, I was assigned to the ICU, mainly responsible for guiding other doctors to carry out tracheal intubation, deep vein catheterization, lung, lower limb deep vein, heart ultrasound technology application and teaching; To guide the tasks of Sedation, cardiovascular function regulation, Stress Suppression and Cooperative Tissue Rescue After tracheal intubation.

Deep Vein Catheterization and tracheal intubation are all routine procedures in anesthesiology department. On weekdays, everyone in the operating room is familiar with the whole procedure, but here, the same procedure, difficult and dangerous at the same time

First of all, the ICU of Huoshenshan hospital belongs to the red zone, entering the red zone requires strict self-protection, layer upon layer of protection equipment behind, movement is extremely inconvenient, finger movement is also limited;

Second, endotracheal intubation is a high-risk procedure and carries a significant risk of infection. According to the sixth edition of the diagnostic and therapeutic guidelines, the virus can be transmitted by Aerosol, and Endotracheal intubation requires the opening of the airway, the possibility of Aerosol production is high, and anesthesiologists need to be close to the patient's nose and mouth when intubating, and the risk of infection is far greater than that of colleagues in other positions;

In addition, all patients receiving intubation in the ICU had unstable vital signs, the airway condition was unknown, and intubation needed to be performed quickly, accurately and stably, unlike in the operating room, you can take your time getting everything ready and intubating carefully.

Here, the anesthesiologist's multidisciplinary, multi functional nature is fully demonstrated: Airway Management, first aid resuscitation, vital signs regulation, perioperative ultrasound, and the use of anesthetics. These are the Armando of the anesthesiologist of our new era, and are part of the shift from anesthesiology to perioperative medicine.

[ Xu Haitao performs bedside lung ultrasound on a patient ]

[ Xu Haitao is undergoing oral tracheal intubation ]

Here, I usually in the hospital in the Department of experience has played an important role: usually in the department, I often responsible for complex thoracic surgery and cardiac surgery anesthesia, transesophageal ultrasound is often used in this type of surgery to see how the heart works, and intraoperative ultrasound is also used to see the lungs, so I'm pretty good with an ultrasound machine. Patients with severe NCP often need timely examination to guide the next step of treatment, and these patients also need continuous high flow of oxygen, transfer to the CT examination room will interrupt their oxygen intake, not conducive to treatment, at this point bedside ultrasound simple, fast, non-invasive, real-time, can be repeated many times the advantages of its hands to become an excellent "weapon. ".

Xu Haitao adjusts the suction machine beside the bed of the mechanically ventilated patient

[ Xu Haitao is performing a deep vein catheterization ]

In the first line of work in the ICU, professor Xu Haitao gradually became a widely trusted "General Practitioner" here: When some doctors are not sure about the intubation, or patients after intubation Hemodynamics unstable, or mechanical ventilation patients agitated Sedation, or patients with suspected thrombosis but can not be sure, everyone will want to ask him to help.

Harvard Medical School

Why can anesthesiologist become"omnipotent doctor"of the popular credit that fights epidemic front?

In 2015, Professor Xu Haitao wrote an article under this title, "80% of the accidents in surgery are related to him! ".

He believes that a good anesthesiologist is a physician first, he needs to understand the systemic organs of the pathology, physiology. A good anesthesiologist must also be a qualified emergency physician. Anesthesiologists are also the best doctors for CPR.

Anesthesiologists must closely monitor the patient's vital signs throughout the procedure, including urine volume, blood loss, fluid replacement volume, fluid speed control, constant monitoring, recording, and so on, the medication should be adjusted according to the procedure and the patient's vital signs to ensure that the patient can ride out the difficulty of the operation smoothly.

Xu Haitao claims in this essay that it is as if

"We have all kinds of Anaphylaxis, including antibiotics, fluids, plasma, colloids... and so on. We also have massive intraoperative bleeding, pulmonary embolism, malignant arrhythmias... all of which require prompt and Split Second action by the anesthesiologist.

You know, the success rate of CPR in the O.R. is much higher than the success rate outside the O.R.

In the eyes of the general public, anesthesia is nothing more than giving the patient a little anesthetic. However, anesthesia needs to be administered individually and precisely based on Hemodynamics data. A good anesthesiologist, in addition to regulating blood pressure and regulating the cardiovascular system, uses a variety of tools to bring the patient's body and internal environment into a very good state."

So, when really on the front line, both anesthesia, first aid and internal medicine and other skills of anesthesiologists, naturally become able to plug the hole of the "general doctor. ".
